LEGISLATIVE BILL 1022
FINAL READING
(SECOND)
Introduced by Murman, 38; Andersen, 49; Ballard, 21; Clements, 2; Juarez,
5; Kauth, 31; Lippincott, 34; Lonowski, 33; Meyer, G., 17;
Storer, 43.
Read first time January 13, 2026
Committee: Education
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to education; to amend section 79-808, Reissue
2 Revised Statutes of Nebraska; to provide an exception for
3 applications for a Nebraska substitute teacher's certificate to the
4 requirement for human relations training; and to repeal the original
5 section.
6 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1022 LB1022
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 79-808, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 79-808 (1) The board shall establish, adopt, and promulgate
4 appropriate rules, regulations, and procedures governing the issuance,
5 renewal, conversion, suspension, and revocation of certificates and
6 permits to teach, provide special services, and administer based upon (a)
7 earned college credit in humanities, social and natural sciences,
8 mathematics, or career and technical education, (b) earned college
9 credit, or its equivalent in professional education, for particular
10 teaching, special services, or administrative assignments, (c) criminal
11 history record information if the applicant has not been a continuous
12 Nebraska resident for five years immediately preceding application for
13 the first issuance of a certificate, (d) human relations training, except
14 as provided in subdivision (2)(b) of this section for an applicant for a
15 Nebraska substitute teacher's certificate or as provided in section
16 79-813 for a military spouse or an applicant who holds a certificate or
17 permit from another state, (e) successful teaching, administration, or
18 provision of special services, and (f) moral, mental, and physical
19 fitness for teaching, all in accordance with sound educational practices.
20 Such rules, regulations, and procedures shall also provide for
21 endorsement requirements to indicate areas of specialization on such
22 certificates and permits. Such rules and regulations shall not require
23 any test of basic skills.
24 (2)(a) (2) The board may issue a temporary certificate, valid for a
25 period not to exceed two years, to any applicant for certification who
26 has not completed the human relations training requirement.
27 (b) An applicant for a Nebraska substitute teacher's certificate
28 shall not be required to meet the human relations training requirement
29 under this section to obtain such certificate.
30 (3) Members of any advisory committee established by the board to
31 assist the board in teacher education and certification matters shall be
-2-

LB1022 LB1022
2026 2026
1 reimbursed for expenses as provided in sections 81-1174 to 81-1177. Each
2 school district which has an employee who serves as a member of such
3 committee and which is required to hire a person to replace such member
4 during the member's attendance at meetings or activities of the committee
5 or any subcommittee thereof shall be reimbursed from the Certification
6 Fund for the expense it incurs from hiring a replacement. School
7 districts may excuse employees who serve on such advisory committees from
8 certain duties which conflict with any advisory committee duties.
9 Sec. 2. Original section 79-808, Reissue Revised Statutes of
10 Nebraska, is repealed.
